<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iran assured Foreign Minister Roland Dumas of France that some Western hostages 
held in Lebanon will be freed soon, the official Kuwait News Agency reported. 
Dumas flew to Kuwait for a brief state visit after a two-day visit to Iran. The 
news agency, quoting diplomats traveling with Dumas, said, "He obtained a 
promise from responsible officials (in Tehran) that a number of Western 
hostages held in Lebanon will be released within a short period." The diplomats 
did not elaborate, the agency said. Most of the 16 missing foreigners, 
including nine Americans, are believed held by Shiite Muslim extremists loyal 
to Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
