<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIS TIME, LAS VEGAS ROUTS UC SANTA BARBARA, 77-61 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara, which upset Nevada Las Vegas twice last season, was no match 
for the Rebels Monday night in the Thomas and Mack Center at Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
David Butler scored 21 points and Greg Anthony added 19 to lead 19th-ranked Las 
Vegas to a 77-61 Big West Conference basketball victory. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels led only 7-6 after 5 minutes, but then outscored Santa Barbara, 
13-0, over the next 4 minutes to gain a 20-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
They gained a 37-24 halftime lead behind Anthony's 14 points. Santa Barbara, 
led by Mike Doyle's 17 points and Carrick DeHart's 13, could pull no closer in 
the second half than the final margin. 
</P>
<P>
Las Vegas is 15-5 overall, 10-1 in Big West play. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara (15-4, 6-4) fell 3 1/2 games behind the Rebels and a half game 
behind second-place New Mexico State (7-4). 
</P>
<P>
Las Vegas opened the second half with strong shooting and quickly took control. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels held a 49-29 lead with 15:30 left as Las Vegas shot 63% and Santa 
Barbara shot a dismal 33%. 
</P>
<P>
Both teams settled down, but Las Vegas held its 20-point margin with Stacey 
Augmon and George Ackles controlling the tempo. Ackles' inside defense 
frustrated Santa Barbara's penetrating offense. He had four blocked shots 
midway through the second half. 
</P>
<P>
So, the Gauchos tried to go outside, but Las Vegas' tough defense denied them 
good shots. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels built their biggest lead, 71-47, on Butler's dunk late in the game. 
But Doyle made three quick baskets and Gary Gray added a jumper to pull the 
Gauchos within 71-55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
