<TEXT>
<P>
The CBS schedule is on the move again. "TV 101," the series set in a 
high-school video journalism class, is moving for the third time, heading for 
Saturday nights at 9 as of Feb. 25. It'll take over the hour currently occupied 
by the limited run of "The Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour." A new series, "Hard 
Time on Planet Earth," will premiere March 1 in the 8 p.m. Wednesday time 
period where "TV 101" has been playing. "Hard Time" stars Martin Kove, late of 
"Cagney &amp; Lacey," as an extraterrestrial convict sentenced to live on Earth 
in human form. "TV 101," produced by Grant Tinker's GTG Entertainment, started 
on Tuesdays and is the only survivor among GTG's three network series that 
premiered this season. ALEENE MacMINN 
