<TEXT>
<P>
Former Israel diplomat and cabinet minister Abba Eban begins work this week on 
a four-segment, 4 1/2-hour PBS miniseries called "Israel 1947 to 1988: A 
Personal Witness." Presented by New York's WNET, it will begin where Eban's 
nine-part series, "Heritage: Civilization and the Jews," ended, with the events 
leading to Israeli independence in 1948. "Heritage" was broadcast by PBS three 
times and was shown in more than a dozen countries. In Tel Aviv on Monday, Eban 
said he will draw on his personal experience to provide commentary on Israel's 
political and military history. The first 90-minute segment is slated for 
completion by fall. ALEENE MacMINN 
