<HEADLINE>
<P>
REAGAN'S $50,000 FEE FOR SPEAKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It amazes me to learn that the Reagans need more money in their retirement; 
they have set astronomical fees for any and all speaking engagements in the 
future. 
</P>
<P>
I wonder what happened to the all-American idea of putting something back into 
the system when one's working days come to an end? Here in Torrance through the 
Retired Senior Volunteer Program, hundreds of retirees are handling community 
jobs with no thought of recompense and enjoying their ability to give back to 
the community something of value. 
</P>
<P>
The Reagans have more than adequate pensions to see them through their twilight 
years and friends made it possible for them to retire to a very fine home in 
Bel-Air with little cost to them. What more do they need? 
</P>
<P>
It is no wonder our young people have warped values when they see what our 
former leaders require for themselves. 
</P>
<P>
IRENE ADAMS 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
