<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN FERNANDO'S MCCRARY TO PLAY FOR CS FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Howard McCrary, a Times All-Valley defensive back for San Fernando High, has 
verbally commited to play football for Cal State Fullerton. The earliest day 
for high school seniors to sign national letters of intent is Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
McCrary visited Pacific 10 Conference schools Arizona State, Oregon, Oregon 
State and Washington, but chose Fullerton largely because of academic problems. 
McCrary has yet to score 700 or better on the Scholastic Aptitude Test and 
therefore has not met National Collegiate Athletic Assn. Prop. 48 requirements. 
</P>
<P>
The Pac-10 schools would accept McCrary on a conditional basis only, but 
Fullerton officials said he will be offered a scholarship even if he enters 
school ineligible under Prop. 48 restrictions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
