<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: AMGEN ADOPTS PLAN TO HAMPER HOSTILE TAKEOVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amgen, the Thousand Oaks biotechnology company, last week adopted a so-called 
"poison pill" provision that would make it more difficult for someone to 
acquire the company. Among other things, if someone acquires 20% or more of 
Amgen's stock, it would allow Amgen's other shareholders to buy additional 
Amgen stock at a 50% discount. 
</P>
<P>
Amgen has several biotechnology drugs under development and is awaiting U.S. 
Food and Drug Administration approval to sell its anti-anemia drug. 
</P>
