<P>
OPENING OF WILDLIFE SANCTUARY DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A wildlife lake and bird sanctuary in the Sepulveda Basin will not be opened 
until the end of the month because of a delay in obtaining a permit from the 
state Regional Water Quality Control Board, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The corps and the city of Los Angeles had hoped to open the lake in January, 
but a meeting to discuss the permit was delayed until Wednesday because some 
participants could not attend, according to Sheila Murphy, a project manager 
with the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy said officials are ready to fill the lake, which would be accessible 
only by hiking trails, as soon as the water permit is granted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
