<P>
DRIVER HELD AFTER CACHE OF MARIJUANA IS FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A driver in Sunset Beach was arrested after 100 pounds of marijuana was found 
in the trunk of his car, California Highway Patrol officers said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
John W. Robinson II, 33, a regular patron of the Best Western Sunset Beach Inn 
in Sunset Beach, had a minor accident Friday night in which his rented 1988 
Bonneville struck another vehicle on Pacific Coast Highway, CHP Traffic Officer 
Richard Hoffpauer said. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson returned to the motel, where an acquaintance noticed that he appeared 
drunk and took Robinson's car keys from him. When Robinson asked to get 
something from his trunk, the acquaintance saw the marijuana and notified 
police. 
</P>
