<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHILDREN RETURNED TO U.S.; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA ANA POLICEMAN ACCUSED IN ABDUCTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TYLER L. CHIN, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 30-year-old Santa Ana police officer, accused of abducting his two children 
from his estranged wife's home after visiting them in northeastern England on 
Thursday, is back in the United States, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Malcolm Lowery has contacted British police and told them that he and his 
children, Sarah Jane, 8, and David Anthony, 7, are back in America and in good 
health, according to Inspector Edward Hill of the Newcastle upon Tyne Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
The children were allegedly taken from the home of their mother, Barbara 
Lowery, 30, at about 8:30 p.m. Thursday, Hill said. "She left the room, went to 
the bathroom, and while she was there he took the children (away) in a car." 
</P>
<P>
Officials on both sides of the Atlantic do not know how Lowery evaded an 
all-points bulletin. 
</P>
<P>
Neither Lowery nor his estranged wife could be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana Police Department spokeswoman Maureen Thomas said Lowery telephoned 
the department Monday. "He's obtained legal counsel, and he's going to be in 
contact with British authorities to resolve the custody situation," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Lowery, who was hired in October, 1987, has been on vacation and is scheduled 
to return to patrol duty next week, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
"Upon his return, his supervisors will discuss the issue and evaluate his 
conduct," she said. 
</P>
<P>
"Basically, the only thing we can say is that British authorities have 
contacted us and said they do not intend to file any criminal charges against 
Officer Lowery," she said. "They feel it's a domestic issue and not a criminal 
issue." 
</P>
<P>
Hill said Barbara Lowery "intends to take legal action to have the children 
returned." 
</P>
<P>
The Lowerys came to the United States from Britain in 1985, he said, adding 
that Barbara Lowery and the children returned home in 1987 because "she didn't 
like America." 
</P>
</TEXT>
