<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
SADDLEBACK STILL ATOP PREP POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saddleback High School, riding a 17-game winning streak, is the top-ranked team 
in the Orange County Sportswriters' Assn. prep basketball poll for the fifth 
consecutive week. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback has the longest winning streak in the county, followed by 
eighth-ranked El Dorado (12) and 10th-ranked Trabuco Hills (11). Trabuco Hills 
makes its first appearance in the poll this week. 
</P>
<P>
In the featured game of the week, third-ranked Capistrano Valley plays at 
sixth-ranked Irvine on Wednesday in a South Coast League game. 
</P>
<P>
The writers' poll: 
</P>
