<P>
Japan's stock-profiteering scandal claimed yet another prominent casualty today 
as the chief of an opposition party resigned over his lucrative dealings with 
the company at the heart of the affair. 
</P>
<P>
Saburo Tsukamoto, 61, chairman of the Democratic Socialist Party, stepped down 
