<P>
Fifteen people were killed and 26 injured when a city bus overturned on a 
winding stretch of road and plunged down a 60-foot cliff, authorities said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Monday about four miles from downtown on a curved, steep 
portion of road near the Valle Verde neighborhood on the outskirts of this Baja 
California resort, Fire Department officials said. A spokesman for the 
department said bus driver Enrique Hernandez de Jesus apparently lost control 
of the vehicle while trying to negotiate the curve. One surviving passenger 
told investigators that the bus driver said, "Hang on tight, I have no brakes," 
moments before the bus slid over the cliff. 
